# Tessera Front Desk — environment template.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in a key. NEVER commit `.env.local`.
# The app and eval both run at $0: the primary path is Google AI Studio's free tier.

# --- LLM provider (pick ONE; Gemini is the primary, free path) ----------------

# 1. PRIMARY — Google AI Studio, native @ai-sdk/google provider.
#    gemini-2.5-flash is on the free tier (~10 requests/min at time of writing),
#    which is why the app and the multi-turn eval both cost $0.
#    Get a key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# 2. FALLBACK — Groq (OpenAI-compatible endpoint), llama-3.3-70b-versatile.
#    Only used when GEMINI_API_KEY is absent. Also a free tier.
#    Get a key: https://console.groq.com/keys
# GROQ_API_KEY=

# --- Database (optional, but RECOMMENDED for production) ----------------------
# Local dev needs NOTHING here: the app defaults to a local SQLite file
# (`file:local.db`) created by `npm run seed`.
#
# In production, set both of these for a hosted Turso database — a PERSISTENT,
# SHARED calendar. WITHOUT them, a Vercel deploy falls back to an ephemeral
# per-instance file (`/tmp/front-desk.db`), auto-seeded on first access, so
# bookings may not survive between requests. Fine for a quick demo; set Turso for
# anything real.
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=

# --- Demo reset protection (optional) -----------------------------------------
# /api/reset wipes and reseeds the shared calendar. In production set RESET_SECRET
# so only you can trigger it: callers must pass `?secret=...` or an `x-reset-secret`
# header. When unset (local dev) reset is open.
# RESET_SECRET=

# The on-page "Reset demo" link is HIDDEN unless this is "1". Leave unset in
# production (a stranger shouldn't wipe the calendar mid-demo); set it locally to
# show the link. It only affects the UI — the route is still guarded by RESET_SECRET.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ALLOW_PUBLIC_RESET=1
